## Always-on conventions

- Match surrounding code: naming, structure, comment density, idioms.
- Prefer reuse over new abstractions. Search for an existing utility before writing one.
- Functions do one thing; keep them small and named for their effect.
- No dead code, no commented-out blocks, no TODO without an owner/condition.
- Files and dirs: kebab-case. Types/classes: PascalCase. Functions/vars: per-language idiom.
- Validate at boundaries (inputs, external responses). Fail fast with actionable messages.
- Never swallow errors silently; never log secrets.
- Every behaviour change ships with a test. Test the behaviour, not the implementation.
- Before adding a dependency, justify it. Pin versions.
- Conventional Commits: `feat:` `fix:` `docs:` `refactor:` `test:` `chore:`.
- Secrets only in `${ENV_VAR}` — never committed. MCP configs use `${ENV_VAR}` placeholders.
- All UI uses design tokens from `product/design-system.md`. Never hardcode colour/spacing/type.

## Context7 (mandatory before any third-party code)

1. `resolve-library-id` with the library name.
2. `get-library-docs` with resolved id, in-use version, and topic filter.
3. Write code against returned docs — not from memory. See `harness/rules/context7-usage.md`.

## Model intent (Cursor collapses tiers to prose intent)

